6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to juvenile bureaus; amending 10A
O.S. 2021, Section 2-4-107, which relates to salaries
8 and expenses; modifying salary limitations; and
providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 10A O.S. 2021, Section 2-4-107, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 2-4-107. A. 1. The salary of the director and other
15 employees of the bureau and any detention home established pursuant
16 to Section 2-4-108 of this title shall be fixed by the judge of the
17 Juvenile Division, subject to the general administrative authority
18 of the county commissioners of the contracting county. The salary
19 of the director shall not exceed ninety percent (90%) of salaries of
20 county Class A officers.
21 2. The salary of any other employee of the juvenile bureau
22 shall not exceed eighty-five percent (85%) of Class A county
23 officers.
24
