1 D. In all counties having a juvenile bureau, the budget of the
2 juvenile bureau for salaries and expenses of the director,
3 counselors and other employees shall be established and funded as
4 follows:
5 1. All expenses incurred in complying with the provisions of
6 this article shall be a county charge or funded by a special sales
7 tax dedicated to juvenile programs and expenses;
8 2. The salaries and other compensation of all employees of the
9 juvenile bureau shall be fixed by the judge within the limit of the
10 total appropriations therefor; and
11 3. It is made the duty of the county excise board to make the
12 necessary appropriation and levy for the payment of salaries of the
13 director and all other employees, together with the expenses of
14 administering the bureau, consistent with the duty to do likewise
15 with the budget estimates of other county officers under the board's
16 jurisdiction, as required by the Constitution and laws of this
17 state.
18 4. Except in instances where it is entitled to representation
19 because of insurance coverage, the district attorney of the county
20 in which the juvenile bureau is located shall represent the juvenile
21 bureau and any employee who was acting in his or her official
22 capacity at the time of the act or omission complained of in any
23 lawsuit. If the district attorney has a conflict of interest or
24 otherwise declines to represent the juvenile bureau or its
